On Tue, 15 May 2007, Mike Soultanian wrote:

> Accessys(-at-)smart.net wrote:
> > I put my races in a plastic bag and put them in the freezer the night
> > before I need to use em.  get everything ready, go get one and quickly
> > slide it in,  work fast but it has always just slid right in.
>
> Ha!  That's a neat trick!

Another approach is to freeze them with dry ice to get them even colder.
A dry ice bath with 95% (not 70%!) isopropyl alcohol will cool the race
down quickly.
If you're a geek like me, liquid nitrogen is even better, but it takes
special equipment to handle.

George
